Key Insights from Analysis

1. High-Risk Patterns

Damaged batteries: Account for 75% of all incidents.
Temperature threshold: 35°C is critical for increased risk.
Response time: Exceeding 45 minutes leads to higher injury rates.


2. Financial Impact
Total damage: $10.1 million
Average per incident: $2.5 million
Damaged batteries: 3.5x higher cost compared to undamaged units.


3. Safety Recommendations
Immediate: Implement temperature monitoring for all storage above 30°C.
Short-term: Establish a damaged battery segregation protocol.
Long-term: Reduce emergency response time to under 30 minutes.